Package: gao
Type: Package
Title: Harvest Government Accountability Office Reports
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person(c("Jack", "T."), "Rametta", email = "jtrametta@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Automates the harvesting and downloading of reports published by
    the United States Government Accountability Office (GAO). Provides
    functions for scraping report page URLs, extracting PDF download links,
    and downloading report files in PDF or HTML format. Requires
    'curl-impersonate' to be installed on the system to bypass TLS
    fingerprint filtering. This package is not affiliated with or endorsed
    by the U.S. Government Accountability Office.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    rvest
SystemRequirements: curl-impersonate (https://github.com/lexiforest/curl-impersonate)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
URL: https://github.com/CetiAlphaFive/gao
BugReports: https://github.com/CetiAlphaFive/gao/issues
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
